import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['income'], data['health'], c=data['region'].astype('category').cat.codes, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.7)
    ax.set_xlabel('Income')
    ax.set_ylabel('Health')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between income and health?')
    
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Regions")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='region', y='income', data=data, palette='Set2')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Income')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Region', loc='upper right', labels=data['region'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
